708617f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 37th Street
708617f-a.text:
Fifth Ave., at the N.W. corner of West 37th Street, showing in a set
of 3 views, different aspects of the Brick Presbyterian Church erected
at this location in 1858 and about to be demolished. This structure
surplanted the original edifice on the corner of Beekman and Nassau
Streets; the latter being erected in 1767. Both of these structures
were identical, though the one here shown is on a much larger scale.
A new place of worship is now under construction at the S.W. corner of
Park Ave. and East 91st Street. No. 1 of this set shows the Avenue
frontage, No. 2 the 37th Street side and No. 3 the door at the rear.
October 1937.
R.W. Hill.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
